The All Progressives Congress (APC) has said the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) governorship candidate, Douye Diri, is “crying wolf” over allegation that it influenced the list of Supervisory Presiding Officers (SPOs) deployed for the Bayelsa State governorship election. Mr Yekini Nabena, APC Deputy National Publicity Secretary, has accused PDP and its candidate of doing everything possible to intimidate the Resident Electoral Commission (REC) into doing their bidding. Nabena, in a statement issued yesterday in Abuja, said PDP and its governorship candidate were crying wolf in the face of its imminent election defeat, come November 16.  Jonathan never contested, won any election even in Bayelsa - Nabena Nabena to Dickson: You can’t rig Bayelsa poll PDP’s claim of rigging in Borno stage-managed – Dalori